#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:69
msgid "Components of a Digital TV card/STB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:71
msgid ""
"A Digital TV card or set-top-box (STB) usually consists of the following "
"main hardware components:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:74
msgid "Frontend consisting of tuner and digital TV demodulator"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:75
msgid ""
"Here the raw signal reaches the digital TV hardware from a satellite dish or "
"antenna or directly from cable. The frontend down-converts and demodulates "
"this signal into an MPEG transport stream (TS). In case of a satellite "
"frontend, this includes a facility for satellite equipment control (SEC), "
"which allows control of LNB polarization, multi feed switches or dish rotors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:82
msgid "Conditional Access (CA) hardware like CI adapters and smartcard slots"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:83
msgid ""
"The complete TS is passed through the CA hardware. Programs to which the "
"user has access (controlled by the smart card) are decoded in real time and "
"re-inserted into the TS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:89
msgid "Not every digital TV hardware provides conditional access hardware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:91
msgid "Demultiplexer which filters the incoming Digital TV MPEG-TS stream"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:92
msgid ""
"The demultiplexer splits the TS into its components like audio and video "
"streams. Besides usually several of such audio and video streams it also "
"contains data streams with information about the programs offered in this or "
"other streams of the same provider."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:97
msgid "Audio and video decoder"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:98
msgid ""
"The main targets of the demultiplexer are audio and video decoders. After "
"decoding, they pass on the uncompressed audio and video to the computer "
"screen or to a TV set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:104
msgid ""
"Modern hardware usually doesn't have a separate decoder hardware, as such "
"functionality can be provided by the main CPU, by the graphics adapter of "
"the system or by a signal processing hardware embedded on a Systems on a "
"Chip (SoC) integrated circuit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:109
msgid ""
"It may also not be needed for certain usages (e.g. for data-only uses like "
"\"internet over satellite\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:112
msgid ""
":ref:`stb_components` shows a crude schematic of the control and data flow "
"between those components."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:120
msgid "Linux Digital TV Devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:122
msgid ""
"The Linux Digital TV API lets you control these hardware components through "
"currently six Unix-style character devices for video, audio, frontend, "
"demux, CA and IP-over-DVB networking. The video and audio devices control "
"the MPEG2 decoder hardware, the frontend device the tuner and the Digital TV "
"demodulator. The demux device gives you control over the PES and section "
"filters of the hardware. If the hardware does not support filtering these "
"filters can be implemented in software. Finally, the CA device controls all "
"the conditional access capabilities of the hardware. It can depend on the "
"individual security requirements of the platform, if and how many of the CA "
"functions are made available to the application through this device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:134
msgid ""
"All devices can be found in the ``/dev`` tree under ``/dev/dvb``. The "
"individual devices are called:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:137
msgid "``/dev/dvb/adapterN/audioM``,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:139
msgid "``/dev/dvb/adapterN/videoM``,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:141
msgid "``/dev/dvb/adapterN/frontendM``,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:143
msgid "``/dev/dvb/adapterN/netM``,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:145
msgid "``/dev/dvb/adapterN/demuxM``,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:147
msgid "``/dev/dvb/adapterN/dvrM``,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:149
msgid "``/dev/dvb/adapterN/caM``,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/dvb/intro.rst:151
msgid ""
"where ``N`` enumerates the Digital TV cards in a system starting from 0, and "
"``M`` enumerates the devices of each type within each adapter, starting from "
"0, too. We will omit the \"``/dev/dvb/adapterN/``\\ \" in the further "
"discussion of these devices."
msgstr ""

